The paper deals with information theoretic principles of denoising, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of latent variable models and dependent component analysis suggests a focus on information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.MM). Additionally, the application of the method to social media platforms and image denoising suggests a possible connection to social media analysis (cs.SI).
